  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2025-02-27",
    "date": "2026-04-13T11:19:55Z",
    "text": "End FEMA Benefits for Illegal Immigrants Act\n\nThis bill prohibits the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) from carrying out the Shelter and Services Program (SSP) and rescinds unobligated funds transferred to FEMA for this purpose for FY2023-FY2024.\u00a0\n\nThe SSP provides grants to public and nonprofit entities for temporarily providing shelter and other services (e.g., food, transportation) to noncitizen migrants released from Department of Homeland Security custody and awaiting immigration court proceedings, as well as for increasing grant recipients\u2019 capacity to temporarily shelter such individuals (e.g., modifying existing facilities)."
  },
